Load SingleCellExperiment data

Source: R/data_loading.R
load_sce_data.Rd

Loads single-cell data from a SingleCellExperiment object or RDS file containing one. Converts the SingleCellExperiment to a Seurat object for pipeline compatibility.

Usage

load_sce_data(
  sce_data_path,
  experiment_id,
  min_cells = 3,
  min_features = 200,
  verbose = TRUE,
  handle_duplicates = "make_unique"
)

Arguments

sce_data_path

A SingleCellExperiment object or character string path to an RDS file containing a SingleCellExperiment object.

experiment_id

Character string specifying the experiment ID for tracking.

min_cells

Integer specifying the minimum number of cells expressing a gene for the gene to be included. Default is 3.

min_features

Integer specifying the minimum number of genes expressed in a cell for the cell to be included. Default is 200.

verbose

Logical indicating whether to print progress messages. Default is TRUE.

handle_duplicates

Character string specifying how to handle duplicate gene names. Options are "make_unique" (default), "aggregate", "first", or "error". "make_unique" appends .1, .2 etc to duplicates, "aggregate" sums duplicate genes, "first" keeps only the first occurrence, "error" stops with an informative message.

Value

A Seurat object containing:

  • Count matrix from the SingleCellExperiment

  • Cell metadata from colData

  • Filtered genes and cells based on min_cells and min_features

Details

The function performs the following steps:

  1. Loads SCE object from file if path is provided

  2. Validates the SingleCellExperiment object structure

  3. Extracts counts and metadata

  4. Converts to Seurat object with appropriate filtering

  5. Preserves sample information from colData

See also

load_10x_data for loading 10X Genomics format data preprocess_data for preprocessing the loaded data

Examples

# Create a small example SingleCellExperiment
if (requireNamespace("SingleCellExperiment", quietly = TRUE)) {
  library(SingleCellExperiment)

  # Generate example count data
  set.seed(123)
  counts <- matrix(rpois(2000, lambda = 5), ncol = 40, nrow = 50)
  colnames(counts) <- paste0("Cell", seq_len(40))
  rownames(counts) <- paste0("Gene", seq_len(50))

  # Create SingleCellExperiment object
  sce <- SingleCellExperiment(assays = list(counts = counts))

  # Add sample metadata
  colData(sce)$sample <- rep(c("SampleA", "SampleB"), each = 20)

  # Load the SCE object into Seurat format
  seurat_obj <- load_sce_data(
    sce_data_path = sce,
    experiment_id = "example_sce",
    min_cells = 3,
    min_features = 10,
    verbose = FALSE
  )

  # Display basic information
  print(seurat_obj)
  cat("Number of cells:", ncol(seurat_obj), "\n")
  cat("Number of genes:", nrow(seurat_obj), "\n")
}
